t5168.text: This was made pretty quick while talking to Pazx the other week about the AUS PR, but hopefully some of you still found it a lil interesting. No, I do not care about, or want you input on this. Unless you are a statistician; I'm happy to talk in the DMs with fellow stats people.

t5169.text: For me PRs are more reflective than predictive, so think of this as representive of the past year of smash AUS has had, rather than a prediction for the future.

t5170.text: @lilfootgirl is the Sun, and everyone on this PR should be thankful for her warmth. @Day_Aus drew the luco and the sun, and would probably make top 10 on an AUS art PR. God bless them both

t5171.text: 1st places were all given an adjusted percentile of 0. So everyone who managed to win a major got a lil boost.

t5172.text: I used percentile placings, as opposed to just rankings. So that the size of the event factored in somewhat. At bigger events the difference between placings is a lowered. So that placing 3rd at BAM is closer to a 1st percentile than a 3rd placing would be at something like OHN.

t5173.text: To be clear, players weren't penalised for attending earlier events, or the down weighted ones. It's just that those results had a lil less influence over their means and variances. Which is why Luco is so high, dispute not attending much recently. He wasn't punished for absence

t5174.text: After the time weighting, some events were down weighted. So MEO and CWC2 were given a 50% weighting for being Sub majors, and OHN was given a 75% weighting (post time weighting).

t5175.text: The influence of each event on the players score was weighted by time (the most recent event was worth 3 times more than phantom) and the time weighting was linear per event.

t5176.text: The model I used just looked at percentile placings (essentially how far you made it through the bracket) of all the majors (except TFC, since it only had 2 shortlisted players). I looked at data from a shortlist of potential AUS PR candidates, then cut it off at Ben Gold .

t5177.text: There's a lil key in the top left of you haven't really read a box n whiskers plot before. I tried to write it without much jargon, so hopefully it makes enough sense. (Upper and lower quartiles are the top and bottom of the boxes)

t5178.text: Alright, here's my PR. It's just ordered by average score, which is probs a fine enough way to order it. But feel to order it by anything else. By lowest upper quartile, which emphasizes busters; by lowest lower quartile, which emphasizes peeks; or just by your favorits colour.pic.twitter.com/a2hFqycmL9
